text: Thank you everyone for joining our little giveaway, everyone's entries were so entertaining! We have decided @yourbrothefrenchie , your story had us #rofl and so the @lickimat.singapore is yours! 👏🏻👏🏻👏🏻We will be in touch via DM so do check your inbox.

Being an adopted kid that suffered from abused previously, I’m extremely not affectionate. I don’t like hugs not do I give kisses. But that day I was licking my pawmie’s mouth like crazy cause she was eating durian (which was my favourite fruit ever). It was so ticklish that she kept laughing. And even though I was tricked to show affection, I guess any form of affection for my humans are better then nothing at all ☺️

One fine day, mom accidentally left the toilet door open, so it was my chance that I’ve been waiting for a longgg time... I pry open the door slowly, and made sure nobody was looking and went to grab the toilet roll by my mouth. I then ran out and went all around the house with the toilet roll in my mouth. So basically, I was making my whole house a mummy and wrapping it up with toilet roll. When mom came out of her room, she was shocked with the mess I created and started screaming at me. I then went under the sofa to hide.. but I guess humans also win? They just got their ways around with me by luring me out with some treats. She then placed me in the naughty corner and cleaned up the place. 😆😈🤪

Not sure if he’s happy or throwing a tantrum hahah . #circuitbreaker @zumvet @woofalicious.sg @lickimat.singapore

My dog was so exciting running at home that he ran smack into my floor fan. He was dazed for a moment but continued. Toy poodles are smart yet can be dumb at the same time haha 😂😛🤣😋😅😎
